<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Vorticon</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-11 15:07:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is not a hard item to acquire if, as previously stated, you have one or two lvl 50 friends to keep the specs off the Sentry's back.<BR>
The quest in Erudin more often results in the Deep Six Cutlass, a very nice 1hs weapon, but is much harder than doing the Sentry quest. You don't have to initiate this quest in FP, just get the sentry to spawn by talking to the sisterhood leader, have someone kill/train all the spectres on the island, and wait. About 15 minutes after she runs up the hill and stands there for a while, she says something like "Thanks, I found this on a dead Erudite Paladin, here ya go". You DON'T have to keep killing the spectres, because they don't attack her if they respawn and she's standing there, but they CAN'T be there when she first runs up the hill. <BR>
<BR>
Also, IMHO the reason stamina drops so fast with this weapon is because it swings so fast(Del 40). Therefore, you just end up swinging it more for the amount of time you're fighting. Try fighting with a GZ, which isn't that heavy, and you'll see your stamina drop just as fast, because of the low delay. Of course, I could be wrong. :)</font></td></tr></table>
